There are a number of editors available with the default installation:

    Command line
        nano (default) - basic, more similar to modern text editors
                         config file: ~/Workspace/__space__/.dotfiles/config/nano/.nanorc
        vim            - advanced text editor with a focus on customizability and productivity
                         config file: ~/Workspace/__space__/.dotfiles/config/.vimrc
                         config source: https://github.com/amix/vimrc
    
    Code
        Pycharm - IDE for professional Python development
        Webstorm - JavaScript IDE
        Rider - .NET IDE
        IntelliJ IDEA - Java IDE by JetBrains
        CLion - C and C++ IDE
        AppCode - IDE for Swift, Objective-C, C, and C++ development
        Goland - A Go IDE with extended support for JavaScript, TypeScript, and databases
        RubyMine - The most intelligent Ruby and Rails IDE
        Fleet - Next-generation IDE by JetBrains
        Android Studio - Tools for building Android applications
        Visual Studio Code - lightweight, extendable editor; support for many langauges from extensions
        Arduino IDE - Electronics prototyping platform
        MARS - Mips Assembly and Runtime Simulator
        RStudio - Data science software focusing on R and Python
        Mu - Small, simple editor for beginner Python programmers and CircuitPython/MicroPython
        Eclipse - Eclipse IDE for Java developers
            
    Photo
        Adobe Photoshop - Edit, composite, and create beautiful images
        Adobe Illustrator - Create beautiful vector art and illustrations
        Adobe Lightroom - Edit, organize, store, and share photos
    
    Video
        Adobe Premiere Pro - Industry-standard pro video and film editing
        Adobe Media Encoder - Quickly output video files
        Adobe After Effects - Cinematic visual effects and motion graphics
    
    Audio
        Adobe Audition - Bring stories to life with audio
        Audacity - Multi-track audio editor and recorder
        Bfxr - program for people looking to make sound effects for computer games
        Bosca Ceoil - A free easy to use tool for creating music
        
    Text
        Notion - App to write, plan, collaborate, and get organized
        LibreOffice - Office suite
        Sublime Text - Text editor for code, markup and prose
        Atom - Text editor
        MacTeX - Full TeX Live distribution with GUI applications
        MacDown - Open-source Markdown editor
    
    Game Dev
        # Blender - 3D creation suite
        Sweet Home 3D - Interior design application
        Tiled - Flexible level editor
        Godot - An open source game development engine
        Unity - A cross-platform game engine
        Unreal Engine - A 3D computer graphics game engine by Epic Games
    
    Other
        Adobe Acrobat - software to view, create, manipulate, print and manage PDFs
        Numi - Calculator and converter application
        MuseScore - Open-source music notation software
        MagicaVoxel - 8-bit 3D voxel editor and interactive path tracing renderer
        Balsamiq Wireframes - UI wireframing tool
        Beekeeper Studio - Cross platform SQL editor and database management app
